	Second Technical Co-founder</p>
<p>
	Location: Chicago or Seattle<br />
	(Willingness to move once funded)</p>
<p>
	No or little cash compensation<br />
	Compensation will be with equity in the company</p>
<p>
	Are you smart, entrepreneurial, passionate about open source technology (especially Drupal), highly motivated, and ready to join an exciting startup that has the potential to change how investment research industry functions? Look no further&hellip;</p>
<p>
	After the 90 days trial period, you will receive equity partnership in the company. A person with the right fit may also receive minimal monetary compensation (but not primary mode of compensation). This is truly an exceptional opportunity to get involved with a high potential start-up at the ground floor.</p>
<p>
	We are seeking a highly talented developer/coder who has deep technical skills (hacker), who is able to dream like an entrepreneur, and wants to be part of the next revolution of online equity research industry. TheStreetHub.com team is looking for a second technical co-founder to join our founding team that includes a Drupal developer, an online-marketing expert and an industry/domain expert. Our ideal candidate will:</p>
<ul>
	<li>
		Have experience working within an iterative or agile rapid delivery process.</li>
	<li>
		Write clean, well-engineered, test-driven code that conforms with accepted standards within the Drupal community.</li>
	<li>
		Communicate effectively with other team members and/or any third parties contracted</li>
	<li>
		Have a diverse background in supporting technologies such as Linux, MySQL, Apache, PHP, Python, etc.</li>
	<li>
		Understand application design patterns and architecture for interactive, user generated sites.</li>
	<li>
		Have comprehension of, and adhere to the best practices in secure Drupal development.</li>
	<li>
		Have strong abilities in advanced module development and custom theming (including jQuery and CSS).</li>
	<li>
		Have knowledge of common development techniques, including the following:
		<ul>
			<li>
				proficient with, or willing to learn GIT for distributed version control, code checkout and deployment.</li>
			<li>
				troubleshooting and debugging.</li>
			<li>
				web server &amp; database scalability and high availability.</li>
			<li>
				Have used, and familiar with Drush</li>
		</ul>
	</li>
	<li>
		Be able to work without direct supervision, and make use of our internal project management tools.</li>
	<li>
		Provide documentation as required and participate in code reviews, planning sessions and scheduled status updates.</li>
	<li>
		Be familiar with Drupal 7, and able to upgrade modules from previous version.</li>
</ul>
<p>
	MOST IMPORTANTLY, this person needs to be interested in the investments, stock market, equity research, public stock market and a founder type that can dream big</p>
<p>
